  • Interface Summary

    ICollection
    Interface to add object and get one if need be

    Will let the user turn left or right
    Iterator

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ant
    The ant class sets up the only object that is steerable
    CustomButton
    Created a custom button class so I can just call a new version without having to type it out multiple times
    Fixed
    Will only let color and size pass through to game object since any object that is fixed cannot move.
    Flag
    The flag class is simple and has location, size, sequence number, and location
    FoodStation
    The food station is fixed and can be varied in size
    Game
    this class implements the Game method to start the game
    GameObject
    Class GameObject sets up the location using the X and Y axis points It will make sure that the object is within parameters It will also be the one to actually set the size and color instead of passing it to a parent class
    GameObjectsCollection
    This will collect all the game objects and insert them into a vector
    GameWorld
    GameWorld will create instances of all the game objects needed to populate the game world
    MapView
    This will set the Map view settings for the gui
    Movable
    This will allow any of the concrete classes move within the game world
    ScoreView
    This will create and populate the stats bar on top
    Spider
    The class spider is a concrete class to be added in gameworld as an object
